headline: Super Micro Computer (SMCI) Week in Review: 11% Stock Drop Despite 123% Growth
summary: Super Micro Computer (NASDAQ:SMCI) dropped 11.2% this week, closing at $30.54 on Friday. The decline stands out against the broader market’s modest pullback. The S&P 500 (NYSEARCA:SPY) fell 1.3% and the Nasdaq-100 (NASDAQ:QQQ) dropped 1.3% over the same period. Despite the weekly selloff, SMCI remains up 4.3% year-to-date.
